    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-01-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-01-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="61"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Governor of Pennsylvania</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-01-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 8, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to your letter of December 24, circumstances now require the report
                    which it was thought might be delayed without objection. Please forward to me
                    the reports you have in regard to the killing and wounding of Austro-Hungarians
                    near Hazleton. They are necessary to enable the Federal Government to deal with
                    the international aspects of the case, but will not be made public pending the
                    trial of the sheriff and his deputies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>John Sherman.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
